            <abstract id="ref1" label="Abstract">There are letters, reports, and photographs relating to his work in coal research. There is much correspondence concerning research at Bell Telephone Laboratories and Carnegie Institute matters relating to coal technology and machinery and to the steel industry. There are also several photographs, taken shortly after World War II, showing the industrial destruction in Germany.</abstract>
